      "1-hour fire watch initiated at 0754 hours",
      "CO2 fire suppression system activated in generator enclosure"
    ],
    "summary": "On 24 December 2023 at approximately 0743 hours, a fire occurred on a rental air compressor used for blasting and painting operations on the Who Dat floating production unit in MC 547 A. The fire was caused by failure of a 90° elbow on the oil separator piping, which sprayed oil onto hot surfaces within the air compressor enclosure, igniting the oil. The platform's ESD system activated, shutting in the facility. The fire was extinguished by the Lead Operator and Fire Team using water monitors, deluge system, and hose reels. The CO2 fire suppression system in the adjacent generator enclosure activated as designed. No injuries, environmental impact, or platform damage occurred. The rental air compressor sustained fire damage and was removed for repairs costing $31,969.09.",
    "recommendations": [
      "No recommendations issued by BSEE New Orleans District"
    ],
